de.wwu.muggl.symbolic.generating
Class GeneratorChoicePoint

java.lang.Object
  de.wwu.muggl.symbolic.generating.GeneratorChoicePoint
All Implemented Interfaces:
ChoicePoint
public class GeneratorChoicePoint
extends java.lang.Object
implements ChoicePoint

The ChoicePoint is used aside with variable generators. Generators can be used to generate a sequence of variables which should be used one after the other. A generator choice point can be created so backtracking and restarting the execution with the next value provided is possible.

Version:
1.0.0, 2010-03-16
Author:
Tim Majchrzak

getPcNext

public int getPcNext()
Return the pc of the instruction directly following the choice point's instruction. pc and pcNext are equal, as the instruction generating this choice point has to be executed again in any case. While instructions for conditions usually require the execution to be continued after the generating instruction, generator choice points are needed by load instructions which need the right input in the local variables when executed.

Specified by:
getPcNext in interface ChoicePoint
Returns:
zero, as an int value.

applyStateChanges

public void applyStateChanges()
Apply any state changes required for the current choice. This will set the generated value as a local variable of the frame. Be sure to call this method after preparing a new value via changeToNextChoice(); and of course after using hasAnotherChoice() to find out if there is another choice at all.

Specified by:
applyStateChanges in interface ChoicePoint
Throws:
java.lang.NullPointerException - If no new value has been prepared yet of if there are no more values to be applied at all.
